Clinical scores and algorithms play a central role in modern patient care derived from evidence-based medicine. Evidence based medicine provides guidelines to physicians aimed at improving efficacy and safety of patient management. An international expert panel has developed this application that compiles, in a clear and simple way, most recognized and useful clinical scores and diagnosis algorithms in the field of Thrombosis and Haemostasis.

The use of score calculators and algorithms can facilitate decision making in both diagnosis and treatment of thrombotic and bleeding problems and improve diagnosis accuracy and patient stratification.

Each algorithm includes the indication and a brief interpretation emphasizing the most relevant aspects of each one, followed by some representative references.

We hope this application may guide the clinician in the most appropriate diagnostic and therapeutic strategy, answering some of the questions that may arise when treating thrombotic and bleeding problems.
